---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const pathWithBase = (path: string) => `${base}${base.endsWith('/') ? '' : '/'}${path}`;
const homeHref = pathWithBase('');
const zhStart = pathWithBase('zh/guides/overview/');
const zhExercise = pathWithBase('zh/guides/guardrails/');
const demoHref =
  'https://github.com/2023Anita/openai-agents-medical-research-guide/blob/main/examples/medical_research_agent_demo.py';
const repoHref = 'https://github.com/2023Anita/openai-agents-medical-research-guide';
const remixHref =
  'https://github.com/2023Anita/openai-agents-medical-research-guide/blob/main/docs/fork-and-remix.md';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Case Study | OpenAI Agents SDK for Medical Research</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A portfolio case study on turning an OpenAI Agents SDK tutorial into a GitHub-native interactive AI course lab."
    />
    <meta property="og:image" content={pathWithBase('portfolio/case-study-cover.svg')} />
    <link rel="icon" href={pathWithBase('favicon.png')} />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="case-shell">
      <nav class="case-nav" aria-label="Case study navigation">
        <a class="brand" href={homeHref}>
          <img src={pathWithBase('logo.png')} alt="" />
          <span>OpenAI Agents SDK for Medical Research</span>
        </a>
        <div class="nav-actions">
          <a href={zhStart}>Course</a>
          <a href={repoHref}>GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </nav>

      <section class="case-hero">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Portfolio case study</p>
          <h1>From slides to GitHub-native interactive AI course labs.</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            This project reframes technical teaching as a product: learners read a concept, answer a
            checkpoint, inspect runnable code, fork the repo, and rebuild the course for their own
            research or teaching context.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button primary" href={zhStart}>Start learning</a>
            <a class="button secondary" href={zhExercise}>Try a checkpoint</a>
            <a class="button secondary" href={remixHref}>Fork/remix path</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <img
          class="hero-visual"
          src={pathWithBase('portfolio/case-study-cover.svg')}
          alt="Portfolio case study cover showing the course lab positioning"
        />
      </section>

      <section class="section two-column">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Problem</p>
          <h2>PPT is too passive for fast-moving AI technology.</h2>
        </div>
        <p>
          Agents SDK concepts change quickly and only become clear when learners can run the shape of
          the system. A slide deck can explain the vocabulary, but it rarely leaves students with a
          reusable artifact. This project turns the lesson itself into a working repository.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="proof-grid" aria-label="Portfolio proof">
        <article>
          <span>01</span>
          <h2>Interactive Learning</h2>
          <p>Each chapter includes a static checkpoint with immediate feedback and local completion state.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>02</span>
          <h2>Forkable Course Lab</h2>
          <p>The repo is structured so learners can replace the scenario and publish their own version.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>03</span>
          <h2>Safety-first Medical AI</h2>
          <p>The project teaches research assistance, not diagnosis, treatment, triage, or medication advice.</p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="section visual-section">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Teaching insight</p>
          <h2>The learning unit is a loop, not a lecture.</h2>
          <p>
            A strong AI course now needs a product-like rhythm: concept, decision, feedback, code, and
            remix. The checkpoint is small on purpose. It makes the learner stop, choose, and verify a
            concrete SDK judgment before moving forward.
          </p>
        </div>
        <img
          src={pathWithBase('portfolio/learning-loop.svg')}
          alt="Learning loop diagram showing read, answer, check, and remix"
        />
      </section>

      <section class="section visual-section reversed">
        <img
          src={pathWithBase('portfolio/agent-architecture.svg')}
          alt="System map for the medical research agent course"
        />
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Product shape</p>
          <h2>One focused project carries the whole SDK mental model.</h2>
          <p>
            Instead of teaching Agent, Runner, Tools, Sessions, multi-agent orchestration, Guardrails,
            and Tracing as disconnected API pages, the course binds them to a medical research assistant
            workflow that a learner can inspect and run.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section visual-section">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Remix path</p>
          <h2>The final outcome is a visible public fork.</h2>
          <p>
            The project intentionally includes a fork/remix guide and a course template. That makes it
            easier for students to turn the same pattern into nursing research, pharmacy research,
            public health, or a completely different AI course.
          </p>
        </div>
        <img
          src={pathWithBase('portfolio/fork-remix-flow.svg')}
          alt="Fork and remix flow diagram"
        />
      </section>

      <section class="section value-section">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Portfolio value</p>
          <h2>Why this reads as a product case, not a tutorial dump.</h2>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Product judgment:</strong> a clear shift from passive slides to interactive course labs.</li>
          <li><strong>Engineering judgment:</strong> static-first implementation with no backend, login, or API key risk.</li>
          <li><strong>Education judgment:</strong> chapter rhythm, checkpoints, open practice, and fork/remix workflow.</li>
          <li><strong>Domain judgment:</strong> medical research boundary is visible in the site, docs, demo, and contribution guide.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="cta-band" aria-label="Next actions">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Proof links</p>
          <h2>Inspect the product, then inspect the repo.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="cta-actions">
          <a class="button primary" href={zhStart}>Open the course</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href={demoHref}>Read demo code</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href={repoHref}>View GitHub repo</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  :global(html) {
    background: #f7faf9;
    color: #15211f;
    font-family:
      Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
  }

  :global(body) {
    margin: 0;
  }

  :global(*),
  :global(*::before),
  :global(*::after) {
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  .case-shell {
    min-height: 100vh;
    background: #f7faf9;
  }

  .case-nav,
  .case-hero,
  .section,
  .proof-grid,
  .cta-band {
    width: min(1160px, calc(100% - 40px));
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .case-nav {
    align-items: center;
    display: flex;
    gap: 24px;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 28px 0;
  }

  .brand {
    align-items: center;
    color: #15211f;
    display: inline-flex;
    gap: 12px;
    font-weight: 760;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .brand img {
    border-radius: 6px;
    height: 54px;
    object-fit: contain;
    width: 54px;
  }

  .nav-actions,
  .hero-actions,
  .cta-actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .nav-actions a,
  .button {
    border: 1px solid rgba(21, 33, 31, 0.14);
    border-radius: 999px;
    color: #15211f;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .case-hero {
    align-items: center;
    display: grid;
    gap: 42px;
    grid-template-columns: 0.92fr 1.08fr;
    padding: 72px 0 64px;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    color: #238676;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  h1,
  h2,
  p {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(3.1rem, 7vw, 6.6rem);
    letter-spacing: 0;
    line-height: 0.94;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.8rem);
    letter-spacing: 0;
    line-height: 1.02;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .lede,
  .section p,
  .value-section li,
  article p {
    color: #536762;
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    line-height: 1.72;
  }

  .hero-actions {
    margin-top: 32px;
  }

  .button {
    display: inline-flex;
    padding: 13px 18px;
  }

  .button.primary {
    background: #15211f;
    color: #ffffff;
  }

  .button.secondary {
    background: #ffffff;
  }

  .hero-visual,
  .visual-section img {
    background: #ffffff;
    border: 1px solid rgba(21, 33, 31, 0.12);
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 24px 70px rgba(21, 33, 31, 0.1);
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .section {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(21, 33, 31, 0.12);
    padding: 62px 0;
  }

  .two-column,
  .visual-section,
  .value-section,
  .cta-band {
    display: grid;
    gap: 38px;
    grid-template-columns: 0.9fr 1.1fr;
  }

  .visual-section {
    align-items: center;
  }

  .visual-section.reversed {
    grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 0.9fr;
  }

  .proof-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 16px;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    padding-bottom: 62px;
  }

  article {
    background: #ffffff;
    border: 1px solid rgba(21, 33, 31, 0.1);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 24px;
  }

  article span {
    color: #238676;
    font-size: 0.84rem;
    font-weight: 800;
  }

  article h2 {
    font-size: 1.45rem;
    line-height: 1.18;
    margin: 12px 0;
  }

  article p {
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .value-section ul {
    display: grid;
    gap: 14px;
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .value-section li {
    background: #ffffff;
    border: 1px solid rgba(21, 33, 31, 0.1);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 18px;
  }

  .value-section strong {
    color: #15211f;
  }

  .cta-band {
    align-items: center;
    background: #101917;
    border-radius: 8px;
    color: #f8fbfa;
    margin-bottom: 80px;
    padding: 32px;
  }

  .cta-band h2 {
    color: #f8fbfa;
  }

  .cta-band .button.secondary {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.16);
    color: #f8fbfa;
  }

  .cta-band .button.primary {
    background: #57c9b5;
    color: #101917;
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .case-nav,
    .case-hero,
    .two-column,
    .visual-section,
    .visual-section.reversed,
    .value-section,
    .cta-band {
      display: block;
    }

    .nav-actions,
    .hero-actions,
    .cta-actions {
      margin-top: 18px;
    }

    .case-hero {
      padding-top: 42px;
    }

    .hero-visual,
    .visual-section img {
      margin-top: 28px;
    }

    .proof-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .cta-band {
      padding: 24px;
    }
  }
</style>
